text:
more than a dozen catholic and protestant feminist theologians have rewritten key passages in the bible that they believe had been misinterpreted or edited, to create what they say is a more faithful and up-to-date scripture text.
“while some say that you have to throw out the bible to be a feminist, we believe the opposite,” elisabeth parmentier, one of the authors of the project, called a women’s bible, told afp.
the idea was born at the university of geneva, itself once a hotbed of religious reformation, as the adopted home of john calvin, but the authors say they were inspired by a more recent effort. in the late 19th century radical suffragettes produced ‘the woman’s bible’, a controversial text that similarly challenged what the authors felt were diminished roles given to women in the english-language holy book.

for the current effort, which was published in french in october, the academics say that they have taken full advantage of the latest bible scholarship, to remove “the lingering patriarchal readings that have justified numerous restrictions and bans on women” as well as outright mistranslations.

one example is the well-known passage in the gospel of luke, in which jesus and the apostles visit the household of two sisters, mary and martha. in the story, mary is praised by jesus for listening to him at his feet, over her sibling, who is too preoccupied with preparing the house for the guests.
“it says that martha ensures the ‘service’, which has been interpreted to mean that she served the food, but the greek word diakonia can also have other meanings, for instance it could mean she was a deacon,” said parmentier.
another quest has been rescuing mary magdalene, the most-named woman in the gospels, from centuries of inaccurate readings and embellishments that have cast her as a fallen woman or prostitute. “she stood by jesus, including as he was dying on the cross, when all of the male disciples were afraid. she was the first one to go to his tomb and to discover his resurrection,” says parmentier.

the authors also pursued a broader agenda of challenging the use of bible verses “to reinforce the patriarchal view of society with domesticated women”

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: “we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.” documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takers’ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebook’s “platform policy” allowed only collection of friends’ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebook’s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate “information warfare” against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: “we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.” documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takers’ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebook’s “platform policy” allowed only collection of friends’ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebook’s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate “information warfare” against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

breaking news: there are more types of candy apples here than a candy-apple-lovin’ girl like me could ever eat. 
that’s right, my current events have been happily taking place in orlando, florida. first at universal studios, then disney, then my little family’s first trip to animal kingdom, which inspires me to share this fascinating bit... the females of our closest animal relatives, the bonobo, #cometogether to keep their community safe. they do their best to avoid aggression, practice #empathy, hug often, and, when a male in their group demonstrates violence, they team up to do what they must: oust him. 
this moves me. honestly, it fills my eyes with tears and my #heart with #hope. 
if we’ve ever spoken, i’ve probably shared my unabashed loyalty to a book called #thegiftoffear, which reminds us that we too possess animal instincts that serve to protect us. its author, an internationally-recognized safety expert who often speaks on #abuse, asks us to ignore the rules of polite society if it’s what it takes to #stopdomesticviolence. he directs us to speak up, to fight back, to save each other. he says these crimes are predictable and preventable given that they occur “after many warning signs, and after several people are aware of the risk.” his is a call not to be those people, made aware and *still* allowing ourselves to be prey. 
i will never be prey. never again. on the contrary, to this particular apple in my view, in the view of my sisters, i say–– chomp.
.
.
.

características: - composição: 58% poliester e 42% algodão e echimento em 100% fibra de poliester.
- medidas aproximadas: 55 x 25 x 11 cm.
- conservação: lavar com sabão neutro e água fria.
-  não alvejar.
- não lavar à máquina.
- validade indeterminada.

text:
brett kavanaugh? trump? both had been accused of sexual assault, one even 'joked' about it. and yet, had it hurt them at all? no. if it had they wouldn't be in such high positions of power. .
personally i don't think there was enough evidence to do much of anything. however, i saw his testimony and i believe that he was not qualified to hold a position where emotions cannot truly get in the way of a decision. ten minutes in and he was sobbing, as if his entire world had been shattered. however, nothing really happened (to my knowledge). the woman who accused him did, on the other hand, get death threats and had to move numerous times and even leave her family for a while in order to protect them. .
thoughts?
.
hashtags for change!
#metoo #america #rape #sexualassault #pussygrabsback #feminist #womensmarch

text:
"el feminismo es la habilidad de elegir lo que quieres hacer"- nancy reagan.
----
¡holis lectores! buen domingo para todos♡
 hoy les traigo un post diferente, al ser el anteúltimo del año, me surgió la idea de hablar sobre algo que yo considero muy importante : el feminismo. y que mejor momento para hacerlo que al final de un año histórico y con grandes avances para el mismo.
 el 2018 será, sin duda, un año que pasara a la historia. primero, logramos abrir ojos, logramos que muchas personas se sumen al movimiento y entiendan su verdadero fin! se realizaron muchas huelgas y marchas contra el abuso sexual y la igualdad de oportunidades en todo el mundo (ejemplos pueden ser el #metoo o time's up). logramos que el proyecto de ley sobre el aborto legal, seguro y gratuito se debatiera, y aunque no se haya aprobado, obtuvo media sanción, que es un paso grandísimo! y obvio, se volverá a presentar en el 2019, porque tarde o temprano ¡será ley! 💚✊. logramos que miles de mujeres se animen a hablar, contando y denunciando sus historias, porque algo que el feminismo dejó bien en claro es que nos nos callamos más y que entre nosotras siempre va a existir un apoyo, porque la sororidad es nuestro pilar.
 se que todavía falta avanzar mucho, pero no podemos negar que este año dimos un paso bien fuerte y firme. gritamos hasta quedarnos sin voz, por nosotras y las que ya no están. marchamos, bien unidas por lo nuestro. pero lo más importante, nos plantamos y dijimos que no es no. logramos hacerlo temblar, dejando en claro que no se va a caer, al patriarcado lo vamos a tirar! ♡ -sere📚
name: Sere📚 || Bookstagramer

 el 2018 será, sin duda, un año que pasara a la historia. primero, logramos abrir ojos, logramos que muchas personas se sumen al movimiento y entiendan su verdadero fin! se realizaron muchas huelgas y marchas contra el abuso sexual y la igualdad de opounidades en todo el mundo (ejemplos pueden ser el  o time's up). logramos que el proyecto de ley sobre el aboo legal, seguro y gratuito se debatiera, y aunque no se haya aprobado, obtuvo media sanción, que es un paso grandísimo! y obvio, se volverá a presentar en el 2019, porque tarde o temprano ¡será ley! 💚✊. logramos que miles de mujeres se animen a hablar, contando y denunciando sus historias, porque algo que el feminismo dejó bien en claro es que nos nos callamos más y que entre nosotras siempre va a existir un apoyo, porque la sororidad es nuestro pilar.
 se que todavía falta avanzar mucho, pero no podemos negar que este año dimos un paso bien fuee y firme. gritamos hasta quedarnos sin voz, por nosotras y las que ya no están. marchamos, bien unidas por lo nuestro. pero lo más impoante, nos plantamos y dijimos que no es no. logramos hacerlo temblar, dejando en claro que no se va a caer, al patriarcado lo vamos a tirar! ♡ -sere📚

text:
septiembre .- la controversial periodista angie pérez a través de las redes sociales ha hecho de las suyas, dando pie a distintas polémicas, regresó a instagram tras ser sancionada y publicó una lista de venezolanos “enchufados”, entre esos mencionaron a mimi lazo, luis fernando borjas, paula bevilacqua, mónica fernández, vanessa senior, irrael gómez y muchos más. .- fue difundido a través de instagram un video en donde se observa a la actriz dora mazzone relatando su buena experiencia al tramitar su pasaporte en el saime. tras eso  fue señala de ser una enchufada más del gobierno. .- cardi b y nicki minaj protagonizaron una pelea en un evento de la semana de la moda de nueva york. las raperas llegaron a la violencia física y cardi terminó con una herida menor en una ceja. .- el comediante de 81 años, bill cosby, fue condenado a 10 años de cárcel por drogar y abusar sexualmente de andrea costand en el 2004. .- la actriz asia argento, quien lidera el movimiento #metoo fue acusada de abuso sexual de un menor de edad. .- la actriz colombiana eileen moreno dio a conocer el terrible episodio de violencia doméstica del que fue víctima a manos del actor alejandro garcía. .- la actriz mexicana daniela castro fue detenida en san antonio, texas, tras ser acusada de por un supuesto robo en una boutique.  recientemente, un juez la declaró libre de cargos. .- la vida amorosa de justin bieber fue un poco complicada a lo largo del año, pues retomó y terminó su relación con selena gomez, y después tuvo un noviazgo exprés con hailey baldwin, con quien se casó en secreto en el mes de septiembre. .- lili estefan reveló que la separación de su esposo, lorenzo lauces, se dio después que un paparazzi llegó a la producción del “gordo y la flaca” ofreciendo unas fotos de su esposo con otra mujer, imágenes que decidieron comprar para que sus hijos no sufrieran al verlas.  #farandula2018 #resumenfarandulero2018
#escandalos2018

#billcosby
#eileenmoreno
#danielacastro #liliestefan
#elgordoylaflaca #justinbieber #enchufados #venezuela

text: i'm very hard on myself so if you ask me i'd say i haven't had a good year since 2016 (i know everybody hates that year lol but i booked my first 2 costar roles in barry and the deuce, put up my solo show, and got nominated for an audelco). so in my eyes i haven't topped that but 2018 was pretty solid. i was 1 of the 50 black women playwrights selected out of over 200 to have my monologue about the #metoo movement performed in 50in50 at the billie holiday theater. i had my face all over buses, trains, and stations in my first print ad for #hivprep #livingsure. had the best 10 days ever in my first trip to california. from the pool to the mountain climbing i loved it! i launched afro goddess productions! i wrote, edited, and starred in my short film "razor pains" which got into a few festivals/screenings including katra film series. got to play the role of nilene cooper with an amazing cast/crew and director in "you wouldn't expect". got a new manager! and last but not least finished the proof of concept for "#undercoversidechick" written and starring myself with another fabulous crew and director! this was only my top moments! between roommate drama, landlord drama, moving twice, annoying days jobs, and my crazy love life i believe i did okay lol. so blessed to be a creative surrounded by other creatives with the support of family and friends who love me. its getting closer and closer to my 10 year anniversary in nyc and i feel like i'm only getting started! i love the life i live! #bestof2018

text:
i don’t have time to make this post pretty or appealing, as yet again i’m sitting in public trying to focus on work and i am once again on the verge of bursting into tears - all i can think about is how none of my friends understand the situation i’m in and i have barely talked to any of them about this, because even when i first talked to them about this dilemma, i felt so judged. i’ve withdrawn, not even reaching out to them for a month now. they don’t understand the magnitude of this, and how could they? if they’ve never experienced what i have, what we have … i’ve left my ex for 2 yrs now, yet his face still haunts me every day. his (now ex) girlfriend reached out to me 2 months ago to ask for help to leave him - she found my email address after most likely hacking into his account and finding all my emails of pain to him. and now she wants me to help her press charges against him - but i have no evidence, i don’t even have legal citizenship in the country they are now in. since she asked me of this a month ago, i have felt so paralyzed in what to do -- my gut instinct of helping her and also bringing him to justice … vs … my fear of him getting out unscathed and then going after her/myself and our loved ones. i am so overcome with guilt that i can’t focus on work (i’m so terribly far behind!), i can’t focus on anything unless i space out and watch tv shows … every night i have nightmares of him, only to wake up and have constant flashbacks of him ...
—
—
—

text:
大阪私立大教授が複数の学生や教職員の女性に抱きつくなどのセクハラ行為。

教授は大学の調査に
「記憶がない」
「不快な思いをさせていたのであれば申し訳ない」と答えたと記事にありますが、
反省のかけらもなく、無自覚であることは被害者をさらに傷つけます。 「記憶にない」「不快な思いをさせたならごめんなさい」というセリフは教授に限らず、支援現場では良く聞くセリフ。

確かに加害者にとって特別な出来事でなければ記憶には残らない。
産経ニュースでは「酒の席なので記憶がない」と書かれていけれど、ならばお酒を飲まないという選択肢もあったんです。教授は、それを選ばなかったということ。
そして、酔っていても抱きつく相手は選んでいたということ。
酒の席だから許されるものではありません。

学生や教職員を自分の欲求を満たす性的対象としてセクハラ行為を繰り返し、女性の人権を軽んじる教授に対して停職３か月の懲戒処分は軽すぎる。

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
olhe para minha lista de atuações femininas favoritas em filmes que estrearam no brasil em 2018 e perceba a variedade de histórias marcantes que foram contadas nesse ano. da hilária biografia de uma patinadora olímpica à fantasia que nos fez acreditar no amor silencioso entre uma faxineira e um monstro, de uma cantora ingênua na busca de seu sonho a uma mulher implacável incapaz de perdoar e do horror da mãe que vê sua família entrar em colapso ao musical de uma babá mágica que agrupa qualquer lar.
⠀
essas narrativas não atravessaram somente gêneros e temáticas, mas também gerações. acompanhamos a infância de uma criança pobre no quintal da disney, o amadurecimento conturbado de uma adolescente e o casamento de uma esposa setuagenária com um homem controlador. são produções sobre garotas, mulheres e senhoras interpretadas por atrizes cujo talento dá vida a personagens que precisam aparecer com mais frequência no cinema. como frances mcdormand, sem maquiagem, protestou durante seu discurso no oscar 2018, mulheres querem que suas histórias sejam financiadas pela indústria que hesita em ser inclusiva.
⠀
repare que dos dez longas-metragens que cito aqui, apenas um foi dirigido por uma mulher: a greta gerwig de “lady bird”. note ainda, dentro do próprio gênero, que dos dez papéis selecionados nove são de mulheres brancas e magras. a exceção fica a cargo de yalitza aparicio – professora de descendência mixteca, um povo indigna do méxico – que até estrelar “roma” não era atriz e assim se tornou a estrela mais inesperada do ano. e eu sigo sonhando com o futuro em que situações como a de aparicio deixem de ser surpresa e apareçam cada vez mais nas listas de melhores atuações femininas.
⠀
▪️saoirse ronan (lady bird)
▪️yalitza aparicio (roma)
▪️toni collette (hereditário)
▪️emily blunt (o retorno de mary poppins)
▪️lady gaga (nasce uma estrela)
▪️margot robbie (eu, tonya)
▪️glenn close (a esposa)
▪️brooklynn prince (projeto flórida)
▪️sally hawkins (a forma da água)
▪️frances mcdormand (três anúncios para um crime)
⠀

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significan notly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

text:
i never thought i’d have the strength to go public with my experience. i was told no one wanted to hear what happened. i was blamed for what happened. i lived for years in shame and silence.

then there came a time when i realized my voice was more powerful than my silence. from my voice, and the collective voice of survivors around the world, comes powerful change.

i’m honored to stand with these women who started the process of reform by sharing their experiences. i’m proud of all of us for breaking the silence, and we stand for those who cannot. 
#breakthesilence #metoo #enough #survivor @startribune

text_retweet: “the weather was cool, but had not yet turned cold. the sun was shining and the smell of freshly mulched leaves lingered in the air. we were heading for the playground, minding our own business, when i noticed that there were several cars in the parking lot and several men staring in our direction, talking amongst themselves. that was the first moment ever that the hair truly stood up on the back of my neck and my intuition kicked in. i didn’t know how or why, but i knew that those men were dangerous and if we continued to linger at the park for much longer, my grandfather, sister and i were endangering our lives.” -r. macceile 2018 #metoo #love #feminism #feminist #equality #timesup #trump #women #womenempowerment #girlpower #art #selflove #repost #memes #womensrights #resist #survivor #meme #donaldtrump #maga #motivation #inspiration #america #vote #mentalhealth #believesurvivors

text:
in our estimation, 2018 will go down as the year of the alternative fact... 🤔 .
.
.
this became a popular term in us politics, but politics aside, it’s a great reminder of the way some people look at life.  facts aren’t facts and because of that, nothing really matters - or so they would like you to believe. 📚🔍📖
.
.
.
this is where you take control.  this is where you can make a difference.  no matter your political views, socioeconomic status, color, creed, race, religion, sexuality, or any of it, objective reality still exists.
.
.
.
it is our responsibility (mine, yours, and everyone else) to bring logic, reason and #fact back to the forefront.
.
.
.
in spite of alternative facts, 2018 was also a year of #empowerment through the exposure of truth, with the rise of the #metoo movement and large achievements nationally and internationally for the global cannabis movement.  everyday people used their collective voice to affect change.
.
.
.
a large part of any societal change hinges on the words we use.  words are powerful.  they can be uplifting and empowering or they can be demeaning and pejorative. they can help us soar at their best, and they can attempt to stigmatize and debase us at their worst.
.
.
.
in 2019, our goal is to help normalize cannabis users by addressing them correctly:  mom, dad, son, daughter, brother, sister, grandma, grandpa, nurse, veteran, athlete .... patient.
.
.
.
your ambitions, intellect, personality and humanity defy any one reductive narrative or attempt to label you.
.
.
.
you separate facts from alternative facts.
.
.
.
you stand for science, not stigma.
.
.
.
you are #empowered
.
.
.
.
.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
it would be pretty hard to capture my 2018 in 9 pictures. but this is pretty close to accurate.⁣
⁣
i will always choose my children above anything else when it comes to matters of morals & values. this year i did exactly that through continued recovery, the choice to single parent, celebrating their achievements, being a voice for them and taking care of myself.⁣
⁣
i jumped out of a plane both literally and figuratively this year. and i couldn’t be more excited to see where it takes me in 2019. ❤️

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
a bruxa não vai para a fogueira neste livro
autora: amanda lovelace
editora: @editoraleya

aqueles que consideram “bruxa” um xingamento não poderiam estar mais enganados: bruxas são mulheres capazes de incendiar o mundo ao seu redor. resgatando essa imagem ancestral da figura feminina naturalmente poderosa, independente e, agora, indestrutível, amanda lovelace aprofunda a combinação de contundência e lirismo que arrebatou leitores e marcou sua obra de estreia,a princesa salva a si mesma neste livro, cujos poemas se dedicavam principalmente a temas como relacionamentos abusivos, crescimento pessoal e autoestima. agora, em a bruxa não vai para a fogueira neste livro, ela conclama a união das mulheres contra as mais variadas formas de violência e opressão.

dividido em quatro partes (“o julgamento”, “a queima”, “a tempestade de fogo” e “as cinzas”), a bruxa não vai para a fogueiraneste livroé mais do que uma obra escrita por uma mulher, sobre mulheres e para mulheres: trata-se de uma mensagem de ser humano para ser humano – um tijolo na construção de um mundo mais justo e igualitário. “é meu movimento #metoo pessoal”, afirma a autora. “na época em que comecei a compilar os poemas, celebridades como ke$ha e taylor swift estavam falando sobre assédios que sofreram ou mesmo processando seus agressores. elas me inspiraram a escrever sobre como a cultura do estupro moldou a minha vida e as das mulheres ao meu redor.”

text:
because i didn't. and that should be enough. but, clearly, these days, it still isn't enough. so i will tell you my "why". *caveat* i am sharing this not to be political because, let me be absolutely clear, i think we would be witnessing the same outrageous, unacceptable, politically-motivated mistreatment of a sexual assault survivor if this were a democratic president’s nominee with a democrat run judiciary committee. it would be the same. and that is the travesty. so here goes:
.
i didn't report because:
•i was a young woman in college who was far away from home.
•i was scared to death.
•i felt ashamed and dirty.
•i thought people would not believe me.
•i thought it was my fault.
•i didn't want people to look at me and whisper.
•i didn't want to relive it. over and over.
•i knew most women who do report do not get justice.
.
i didn't tell anyone for a long time because:
•it was my story and releasing it was the only thing i felt i had control of in my life.
•i was still ashamed.
•i had seen how other women were treated who told their story, and didn't want that response for my story.
•i chose not to. it was my body. my life. my choice.
.
today was hard for me and for so many other people. i listened to dr. ford's testimony with tears in my eyes. as she retold the story of probably the worst moment of her life it made me relive my own. it took great courage to do this. let me be clear about this.... there is almost no reason i would ever come forward and sit in front of strangers and tell my story and be open to questions about it. almost no reason. but i have to say that if the perpetrator of my sexual assault would be up for one of the most important jobs in our nation then i would absolutely muster up the courage because it would be the only right thing to do.
.
this is why i didn't report. this is why i have kept the truth quiet for decades. it is the same reason men and women who were molested by priests decades ago kept quiet. i just wish  my story (& others’) would be met with the same reaction as the priests’ victims have been. silence does not negate truth. it proves trauma.
.
#whyididntreport #whiteboxlettering #metoo #metoomovement

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
after taking some sleeping pills, i have only one message. #bringbackourhumanity . all the things people ask for my counsel, my assistance and my intervention comes down to a very palpable lack of humanity. 
sexually molesting children, ritualistic killings,  sexual exploitation of teenage students, discrimination & social biases, religious misogyny are manifestations of our eroded sense of empathy and acts of kindness. 
certain acts just shouldn't be done, period. that's what makes us humans, setting us apart from predatory animals. 
back story: coming back from our office carnival, i witnessed someone being burnt alive at 5am today at rawdon street. bunch of people stood by and no one wanted to intervene. i called a police guy to do so and he said the man is dying soon. he just stood unmoved by my words. i was prevented from intervening by my tricycle (keke) driver who was adamant that i might be killed in the process of intervening. 
i'm still replaying it in my head and i feel so angry. 😭😭😭😭😭😭😭 i'm stuck with the question of, is this really what we have come to? i'm not gonna talk about this anymore. i'm done. 
#metoo #teenagepregnancy #saynotochildmarriage #educationnotexploitation #endchildlabour 
#aspiretoinspire #preserveyourworth #takeachance #createyourpath #girlpower  #africanbeauty #happyglow #lovenothate #familygoals #lifeskillscoach #determined #relationshipgoals #bosslady #empowered #predators #jihadists #ignoranceisnoexcuse  #spreadthelove❤

text:
to all the men out there, 
i want to love you.

i want to hold you, 
i want to hear you, 
i want to feel you, 
i want to make space for you, 
i want to hug you, 
i want to nurture you, 
i want to appreciate you.

i want you to break down before me and cry, 
i want you to tell me about your pain, 
i want you to hold my hand,
i want you to tell me what you don’t know, 
i want you to share your heart with me, 
i want you to allow my love to enter.

and may we embrace, forgive, and realize, 
all abuse was a plea for love, 
all hoarding a symbol of emptiness, 
all knowing a sign of unworthiness.

so what may have seemed unfair, 
is now shown to be the divine’s way of giving to those who were less able to give to themselves.

and my perceived victim identity, 
merely a trick to awaken to my own power, 
to help me see beyond manipulation, 
to the truth that i’m in control, 
enabling me to be here now to hold space,
so others can do the same.

what women endured out of love for men and what men inflicted on women out of love and awakening for them, 
can now be brought to the light, 
seen for what it truly is, 
love, in all it’s different forms.

may we all heal to open our eyes to the beauty and perfection before us. 
may we all appreciate each other’s differences in both masculine and feminine form. 
may we all reframe evil into pain, realizing in that way we’re all the same. 
may we all know our value and worth beyond the physical, into the eternal. 
may we all embrace each other and honor the sacrifice and pain we have endured to heal our planet and bring us into an age of peace and prosperity for all beings. 
may we all awaken to who we really are, fall in love with who we truly are, and from that place, greet our fellow human with the vibration of our heart.

text:
#girlpower my favorite piece to date! keep reading!

for a long time i’ve wanted to do a piece that emboldened the female fight. knowing you’re allowed to be confident in your body and that doesn’t mean it’s sexual or an invitation. but art is all interpretation. my art isn’t free from imperfections but neither are we. i painted this for a reason but maybe you view it differently. i’d love to hear how you see it. 
i couldn’t have done this alone. i want to thank @azraelrenee for being an amazing model. she is an awesome inspiration for girls (and guys) everywhere. keep being rad. thanks to @themudcrusher for pushing me to finish this piece. strong females like you are what this is about. for my friends @nadinesinstagram @laurenmcrae311 and @m_hudgins for being awesome sounding boards and inspiration. and to all the strong females in my life, keep fighting, this is for you. 
in the future i will sell this piece and profit will go towards a charity that helps women. if you’re interested, send me a dm, or stay tuned!

text:
- she [rebekah mercer] loved me. she was like, oh we need more of your type on our side!

your type? - the gays. she loved the gays. so did steve [bannon]. he saw us as early adopters. he figured, if you can get the gays on board, everyone else will follow. it’s why he was so into the whole milo [yiannopoulos] thing.

robert mercer was a pioneer in ai and machine translation. he helped invent algorithmic trading – which replaced hedge fund managers with computer programs – and he listened to wylie’s pitch. it was for a new kind of political message-targeting based on an influential and groundbreaking 2014 paper researched at cambridge’s psychometrics centre, called: - computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans. - in politics, the money man is usually the dumbest person in the room. whereas it’s the opposite way around with mercer, says wylie. - he said very little, but he really listened. he wanted to understand the science. and he wanted proof that it worked.

text:
don’t forget about tarc’s ride to safety program this nye. tarc will provide free transportation for anyone who needs to get to the center for women and families.

if you get onto any tarc bus in louisville or southern indiana and tell the driver you need a ride to safety, you will not need money or a tarc ticket; the ride is free. the driver will arrange for a tarc employee to meet the bus somewhere on its route who will transport you in a car to the center for women and families. you can use this free service if you’re by yourself or if you have your children with you.

text:
25/10/2018. foi a primeira vez que falei disto em palco.

aos 11 anos, na mesma altura que tirei as rodinhas da bicicleta, foi-me diagnosticado transtorno de ansiedade. curioso que andar de bicicleta e sofrer de ansiedade tenham tanto em comum: por muito tempo que passe, nunca se esquece.

como sou demasiado competitivo em tudo o que faço, esforço-me muito para ser o melhor na ansiedade. foi por isso que aos 18 anos fiz upgrade da ansiedade para o síndrome de pânico. o cérebro humano foi concebido para ter 3 ataques de pânico durante a vida toda. o caso mais comum é se a casa estiver a arder. já eu, basta-me queimar as torradas.

estudos dizem que 1 em cada 5 pessoas ja sofreu de uma doença mental. não sei, estudos também dizem que 4 em cada 5 estudos são aldrabice. sei que não estou sozinho. perdi conta às mensagens a agradecer os últimos 10 minutos do meu espetáculo. sinto-me egoísta porque fi-lo a pensar só em mim, não para dar voz a alguém.

durante 12 anos guardei isto tudo para mim. em puto quando ia ao pc do meu pai apagava o histórico não por ver pornografia mas porque ia lá pesquisar sobre agorafobia.

em portugal ouvimos sempre os mesmos debates sobre se foi fora-de-jogo do jonas, mas pouco se fala de saúde mental. problemas mentais são sempre “coisas lá da cabeça deles”, mas quando alguém parte um joelho nunca são coisas lá da rótula dele.

numa época com movimentos tão importantes como o #metoo ou #blacklivesmatter, gostava de ver um pela saúde mental. mas um obsessivo-compulsivo como eu demoraria 7 anos só para escolher a hashtag.

hesitei demasiado tempo se deveria partilhar isto publicamente. porque sou homem, branco e heterossexual. nunca tive de lutar pelo meu espaço. sei que sou um privilegiado. não imagino aquilo por que passa um homossexual para “sair do armário”, se a mim que (só) tenho ansiedade já me custa sair de casa.

estou cansado de fazer humor com problemas que não tenho. não me interessa se primeiro vem o leite ou os cereais, primeiro vem sempre a ansiedade.

no meu último post de 2018, chamo à atenção para a saúde mental. da minha aprendizagem, o primeiro passo é pedir ajuda. ninguém aprende a andar de bicicleta sozinho.
name: Guilherme Geirinhas

i want to acknowledge the current context of #metooindia unfolding in the art world, and overlapping with this year’s biennial — especially in light of survivors coming out and sharing their stories on social media, which has at times been negatively received. regardless of one’s issues with callout culture and tone (which i too have at times), that irritation cannot be used to justify an outright dismissal of people sharing their experiences of harassment, assault, and abuse of power. none of these stories surprise me. some i have heard before and know to be true. in a space as hierarchical and unforgiving as the art world, it could not be more important to have safe spaces for survivors to share their experiences. anonymously or not, it takes great courage, and survivors deserve justice. #believesurvivors  #kmb2018 #scorpiongesture #notsurprised  #feminismforever #timesarechangingwhetheryoulikeitornot #galleryespace #studionyc #rubinmuseum #kochibiennial #timesup #amplificationtheory #metoo

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

prior to the company’s role on trump’s election campaign, wylie had been its director of research. recalling his first meeting with bannon, he explained how fashion was one of the many things they examined, along with “judith butler, foucault and nature of our fractured self”. he said the pair discussed the difference between crocs and chanel’s little black dress as analogous for the fashion spectrum – which would become a blueprint for how the firm used fashion preferences later on.

wylie went onto to criticise the fashion industry for creating a “pre-existing cultural foundation which allowed the alt-right to grow over that time period”. he conceded that while cambridge analytica “exploited the cultural narratives that the fashion and culture industry put out”, the fashion industry was responsible for creating those cultural narratives in the first place. he added: “we need new narratives in culture, and to do a better job of showing more diversity” in order to direct politics along a different route.

according to the data obtained (the majority of which came from us users), certain fans of american denim brands such as wrangler, hollister and lee jeans could be more closely linked to low levels of openness and mistrust – and therefore more likely to engage with pro-trump messaging.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

text:
‼️final reminder‼️
tomorrow is the last day to submit your #metoo stories for  metoo: a collection of true story crimes against women. ⚫️if you’re interested in submitting a story or poem but need more time contact me for a deadline extension. 🔴if you need a refresher on the project or you missed my post about it before here’s some info. ⬇️⬇️ 📣my latest project is called “#metoo: a collection of true story crimes against women.”
the book will be a collection of true story experiences written in women’s own words. these poems and stories will chronicle the crimes and the effects that the experiences had on each woman. 🔜 stories and poems will be accepted until december 31, 2018.
if you have a story/poem that you would like to include email me at mchillstromauthor@yahoo.com. ⚫️all stories/poems will be listed as anonymous submissions. ➡️the types of stories i am looking for include personal experiences of:
-sexual harassment -rape/assault -sexual, emotional, or physical abuse
-stalking
-gender discrimination
-i will accept other topics if they fit in with the theme as well. 🔴 through writing about my own experiences i have found peace and strength. i hope others involved will find this as well and that the future readers of this collection will find courage and strength in the knowledge that they are not alone. 💲 proceeds from the sales of this collection will be donated to help sexual assault survivors. 🔴 also within the book there will be a section  crediting tarana burke for creating the me too movement and detailing the growth of the movement over the last decade.
.
.

text:
when a photographer makes a photograph, they create a window into their soul, and then share that view with the world. it’s a humbling thing at times, but i believe that it helps us to better empathize with one another. it’s one of the driving forces behind all of the work that i do. 
this photograph always gets me when i run across it and i thought i’d share it with you all today.

text:
di recente ho finito di leggere donne che parlano di miriam toews, tra i romanzi più belli del 2018. è la storia di otto donne mennonite, analfabete e "senza voce", che decidono di riunirsi per stabilire cosa fare dopo che gli uomini che le hanno più volte violentate verranno rilasciati di prigione.

non è una distopia in stile il racconto dell'ancella o vox ma un racconto tratto da una storia vera realmente accaduta tra il 2005 e il 2009, in bolivia, dove oltre 130 donne vennero narcotizzate e violentate nel sonno da 8 uomini. il romanzo racconta le riunioni di queste donne che si interrogano sulla vita, tra dubbi etici e morali, sugli uomini, sulle relazioni ma soprattutto si interrogano su loro stesse, in un percorso di autocoscienza difficile e travagliato.

donne che parlano si inserisce così nel dibattito sulla violenza di genere e riflette sulle conseguenze, sul patriarcato e il potere della voce. della presa di parola delle donne come forma di riscatto, sopravvivenza e resistenza. superconsigliato! .
.

text:
thank you to the amazing photographer @ken.rochon for this.

2018 has been a roller coaster ride, smiling has kept me focused on the truth and reality of life.

we are travelling through times of great conflict, change and challenge.  2019 welcomes us all to lift our game, collaborate for the good of all and seek wisdom in unlikely places... wisdom found in the chatter of youth of today and the silver elders wise across decades, all equally received, with women and men valuing differences as a positive energy force, in the boardroom and bedroom, people not changing others against their will.

opening our minds, hearts and willingness to serve each have other in families, communities, countries and continents. 🌍🌎🌏 let's move beyond any confusion and find clarity of meaning, live life with loving intentions.

#magicalconversations #soulmatelove #genderdynamics #itstimetotalk #worldharmony #metoo

text:
je salue le travail de @voxvulva sur ce mot "consentement" qui est son 2e poste du 24 octobre dernier. un vrai effort de clarification sur ce terme lors de l'acte sexuel. surtout aller liker son post aussi pour encourager sa démarche. d'ailleurs merci @pmropert pour cette découverte de pépite 🙏. voici sur ce post et comment il nourrit le projet de @orfeas_gotronakis sur oser évoquer un tabou inacceptable sur les agressions sexuelles et le silence des victimes. .
- ce post parle du consentement lors de l'acte sexuel et rappelle tout d'abord la définition de ce terme "consentement". cela donne comme définition " l'action de donner son accord à une action,  à un projet."
.
- puis @voxvulva va citer ce qui au final est un oui ou un non :
oui = oui .... et tout ce qui n'est pas oui = non.
... donc non = non
... peut être = non
... je ne sais pas = non .
... je ne suis pas sûr = non
... pas de parole = non
et finalement... oui = oui.
.
- puis @voxvulva affirme que le sexe passe par une communication claire pour "être certain(e) du consentement de son/sa partenaire" qui va permettre de s'assurer qu'on n'est pas en train de violer son/sa partenaire".
.
- mais précise que le consentement peut évoluer et être retiré à tout moment de l'acte sexuel... on peut changer d'avis... et il faut "respecter cela", sinon c'est un viol.
.
- @voxvulva finit par une précision importante : souvent la vision du consentement n'inclus pas la notion de désir et le parallèle est fait sur l'idée tenace que le désir d'une femme depuis sa plus tendre enfance est bafoué, ignoré,  nié ...
.
🙏 respect pour cette analyse @voxvulva que je trouve d'une grande finesse et faite de manière limpide. je vous invite à profiter de son talent ❤

#plo_society .
prochain post : " c’est une expérience traumatisante, les souvenirs de la victime sont forcément biaisés : faux "
.
(source post de @voxvulva du 24 octobre 2018)
.
collab sur le projet viol sur les scènes @error_system_93 @9_trexx @loubet.patricia et la technique @conc3rto @mickael_nonine

my #topnine hits were all of me learning to take up space and own that space with pride and joy, whether it was my fitness transformations, or work goals met! i worked in hawaii on @hawaiifive0cbs in my first top of show guest, i did countless hours of spin, hiit, yoga, and weight training (targeting your glutes with heavy weights absolutely works wonders), i shot with @mollypanphotography which you all loved. 💓
but there were also life-changing events not pictured here. i also lost two kitty babies, one to old age and cancer, one to the deadly wet form of fip shortly after adopting her, both of which were devastating to me. my #metoo experience was doubted and questioned by now former friends, my integrity was challenged about my adoption of sasha (the kitten with fip) by a now estranged friend whom i had devoted a lot of care and understanding to in her difficult times this year, and i had a rough few months of learning to love myself enough to leave bad situations in order to make space for new better ones. 🙏🏽
if there’s one major lesson i learned this year, it’s that we are each on our own journey through life and sometimes paths diverge and rejoin, and other times they diverge with no intersection in sight, but we all have work to do on ourselves, flaws to work on, grudges to release, habits to change, and sometimes the only person that can help you is the one you can’t run away from: yourself. 🙌🏽
it’s okay if that one friend can’t be there for you. maybe they are battling their own demons and don’t have the strength to take on anything else. you will make new friends. you have other friends you can lean on, too. and you will always have yourself, and your inner reserve of strength that is deeper than you can know. 🙇🏻‍♀️
with that in mind, may those of us who tend to live for others remember in 2019, to also live for ourselves and put ourselves first now and again, and may those who often elevate their own needs above others remember theirs is not always the most pressing or important. we all have intrinsic value and can be stronger when we work together but there may be tasks only we can complete alone. 👬👭👫
🥂 to #2019

text:
heading into 2019 broken, but healing. hurting, but optimistic. a work in progress, but (and most importantly) a little more wise, smart, and more in tune with my self worth. i am not focused on “making 2019 be my year” i’m simply focused on being. the first of the year doesn’t need to be as significant as we make it-everyday is a good day to make a new goal. to start again. always wishing for happiness health peace and reached goals for my friends and family 
xoxo

text:
051 - كريم ألو بروبوليز (كريم دنج النحل والألوفيرا)
🐝🐝🐝🐝🌵🌵🌵🌵
عندما تحتاج إلى أكثر من مجرد مرطب: أحصل على مزيج كثيف من مادة الألوفيرا المثبتة ومن مادة العكبر أو دنج النحل (الموجود في خلايا النحل التي ينتجها النحل ليحافظ على خلاياه)، مع اضافة مادة البابونج التي تعتبر أفضل أنواع الأعشاب الطبيعية للعناية بالبشرة بالإضافة إلى فيتامين (ايه) وفيتامين (إي) كافية للحفاظ على بشرة صحية من الرأس وحتى القدم تمنع حدوث الآفات الجلدية وتعمل على إيجاد طبقة عازلة حامية للجلد وحاجز إضافي للدفاع عن الجسم
مفيد لمعظم مشاكل البشرة وخاصة حب الشباب ويعتبر مرهم مناسب لإلتهاب البواسير

text:
its a special kind of sunday morning when a message pings in.

i love it that still the haters keep on coming with their 'opinions about what i am and what i have 'done ', each one choosing a bit of my story to challenge.

accusations of will tampering, theft, lies and daring to go to the cinema after my nan died!
he didn't go so far to say i ate babies and murdered cats for pleasure, but, hey give it time, .......... it's strange how they believe one thing and then challenge other ridiculous details which they put a whole new spin on to make it suit their opinions!

i feel sorry for them all that have have not the ability, intelligence nor empathy to accept that our lives were different, that there were things they never knew and situations which they could never have grasped because they didn't walk my shoes.

having empathy and the ability to acknowledge other's opinions is a gift and one which is not rife in my birth gene pool, but one which is thankfully present in abundance in the friends and network who i chose to be part of.

i don't feel the need to respond to their poison, but have taken steps today to stop their lies, malicious postings and blatant bullying.

it's been a steep learning curve for me in 2018, learning to hear their noise and change it into beautiful music as i spread my message to other survivors of adversity and abuse that when you know your truth and feel at peace with it you will be strong and passionate in your path to speak out and help other's. 
my voice may shake, along with my knees yet my truth remains.

#survivors #metoo #timesup #warriors #memoir #mytruth #raiseourvoices #perception #endviolence 
@dailyhappytimes @rsvpwm @womenshealthuk @forwomenwhoroar @unwomen @you_are_not_crazy @womenshealthmag @oprah @forgivenessproj @womenwithgifts @lorraine

text:
en mujersana abordamos temas preventivos porque creemos que son la clave para mantener un estilo de vida saludable. también nos gusta compartir post que generen conversaciones sobre temas relevantes que en este año, que ya está terminando, han formado parte de movimientos como #metoo #timesup #hollaback #niunamenos y #escúchametambién⠀
⠀
seamos siempre promotoras de mensajes positivos y empecemos a ser mujeres que tomamos decisiones pensadas en tener una vida más sana. creamos en nosotras mismas y a través de acciones, sin importar lo pequeñas o sencillas que sean, cambiar de forma positiva nuestro entorno.⠀
⠀
tal vez nuestras metas para el próximo año sean muy similares o muy convencionales: voy a comer mejor, voy a tomar más agua, voy a reducir mi estrés, haré ejercicio. qué tal si nos proponemos llevar estas acciones a un paso mayor y seguir llenándonos de mucho amor, gozar de la vida, aprender a sonreír cuando quizá me siento en situaciones de vergüenza; a lo mejor ese rato incómodo hasta se vuelve una nueva anécdota.⠀
⠀
¿qué nos dices de tu plan para este 2019? ¿qué tienes pensado para el nuevo año? ¿algún reto o desafío por allí que nos quieras compartir? seguro alguien más quiere cumplir ese mismo objetivo y qué mejor forma de hacerlo que compartiendo con más mujeres de forma positiva.

text:
you forgot to have fun. huh?

you been hustling and failing and winning all 2018.

looking at the past, measuring the goals, murdering yourself to hit a weight loss objective and you have been killing yourself.

in the process of doing all this stuff...somehow, some way, you forgot to have fun...huh?

i said this to myself. if one of your goals for 2019 is not having a fuggin blast then what the hell are you doing it for.

soooooo i walked my big ass in the lego store (with a beautiful little boy i was taking care of). as they looked up at me like i was godzilla in japan, i realized a couple things. 
1. i get a kick out of being godzilla
2. have some fuggin fun.

so i stopped showing him stuff...and started to just play myself. 
i grabbed wigs and arms and legs and feet and income tax returns (joking) but in grabbed all that stuff and really just had a moment for myself. it was dope!!! dont forget to have fun along the way. your spirit requests it.

have fuggin fun, that's how to be a firestarter!!! .
.
.
.
.

text:
yesterday was my last day as a hairdresser. i was holding back tears when i was clearing out my station as i thought about what this place has been to me for the last year and a half. it never felt like work when i came in. i am so blessed to have had so many wonderful people pass through my chair. i will cherish these friendships for a lifetime. don’t think just because i don’t work with y’all anymore that you got rid of me! i will definitely be crashing the christmas parties! 🤣 thank you guys for making this an amazing place to come to everyday. although i will be sad to leave y’all i’m excited to be home with my son and can’t wait to see what god has in store for us this upcoming year! .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
two child refugees held in us custody died in the space of a month. the first was a girl who travelled for over a week with her father to escape poverty. when she arrived at the border she was detained and not given any water, and later died of dehydration and exhaustion. the second was a boy who also travelled from guatemala. he died of pre existing health issues. however, he wasn’t provided with proper care or medical attention. these children were innocent, they did nothing wrong. yet there are still people who would rather give money to build a wall and prevent an imaginary threat than help prevent innocent children dying. immigrants and refugees aren’t a threat, the us is.

text:
défi jours 5 réussi ! du moins jusqu'à cette fin de journée. mais comme vous pouvez le voir ça monte très très vite les quantités de sucres ! pour le coup il ne me reste plus beaucoup de marge pour ce soir car j'en qui déjà a 22g de sucres sur les 30g maximum recommandés par l'oms ... 😱😱😱 du coup je vais surement devoir faire une croix sur le pain et mon verre de vin 🍷... 😋😋😋 .

10h petit dej: une barre substitut de repas de chez www.enjoyed.fr avec 1 café.
.

14h30 midi : avec un gros rhume j'avoue ne pas avoir bien faim. j'ai donc pris juste un sachet repas vegan de chez @enjoyed.fr (au lieu de 2 normalement recommandé pour faire un repas entier) accompagné d'une pomme. comme ça au moins j'ai eu mes apports en vitamines et en protéines mais tout en étant léger. c'est cool. 😊
.
18h goûter : une barre stoats de chez enjoyed.fr. je prend quasiment que ça au goûter car elles sont sans sucre ajouté et assez nourrissantes pour tenir jusqu'au repas du soir. donc le sucre contenu dans la barre vien juste des aliments et pas de la "merde" rajouté ! donc au moins c'est mieux assimilé par le corps et pas stocké.😉 .
.

et vous quels sont vos trucs et astuces pour limiter votre absorption de sucres ? 🍬🍭🍫🍩
.

text:
🌈
صحنه‌ای از فیلم دختر دانمارکی 
#بخش اول
انسانهایی که صفر و یک نیستند!

احتمالا چندسال اخیر خیلی از مباحثی که در دنیا بحث شدند رو مطالعه کردید و یا برخورد کوچکی باهاش داشتید. مباحثی مثل این که «اصلا چرا باید از نظر جنسیتی دوگانگی داشته باشیم؟» و «فراتر از دوگانه بودن جنسیت». هرقدر در محتوای فارسی جست و جو کردم به جز یکی دو تا وبلاگ قدیمی، چیزی در مورد این مساله پیدا نکردم. بنابراین تصمیم گرفتم این مطلب رو اینجا بنویسم.

چند تعریف ساده در ابتدا

در اینجا چند تعریف خیلی ساده رو با هم بررسی می‌کنیم، سپس به تعریف و داستان سرایی در مورد یکی از تعاریفی که مطرح کردم، می‌پردازیم. این تعاریف مهمن چون بسیار زیاد دیدم که با هم اشتباه گرفته میشن.

جنس : جنس، تعریف بیولوژیکی ما از خودمونه. یعنی چی؟ یعنی این که ما بر اساس اثرات کروموزم ها و هورمون ها در دوران جنینی چطور هستیم. جنس، از نظر بیولوژیکی میشه نر، ماده و بیناجنسی (که مساله بیناجنسی - که اشتباها «دوجنسه» هم بهش گفته میشه) عنوان میشه. پس حتی در این ابعاد هم ما صفر و یکی نیستیم.

جنسیت : جنسیت، ابعاد غیر فیزیولوژیکی و وابسته به شرایط روحی فرد، همچنین ترجیح و انتخاب خود فرد میتونه باشه. جنسیت چندتاس؟! چیزیه که میخوایم درموردش بحث کنیم! پس بذارید ادامه مطلب توضیح بدم.

گرچه تعاریف دیگری هم بودند، ولی این دو تعریف برای این مطلب به نظرم کافی و لازمن. نیازی نبود که حتما سایر تعاریف رو در این مطلب، بیان کنم. در ادامه، قصد داریم مبحث جنسیت رو کمی بیشتر بررسی کنیم!
ادامه در پست #بعدی 
#lgbt #dysphor1a #metoo

text:
🌈
#بخش دوم 
به راستی، چندتا جنسیت داریم؟

ما جنسیت رو نمی‌تونیم دودویی طبقه بندی کنیم، اما ما دسته‌بندی هایی از جنسیت داریم که در ادامه توضیحشون میدم.

همسوجنسیت (cisgender) : این دسته افراد، افرادی هستند که جنسیت و جنسشون، همسو و هم‌جهته. یعنی چی؟ یعنی شخصی بدن نر داره و خودش رو مرد میدونه. این شخص میشه یک مرد همسوجنسیت. در واقع اکثریت (طبق آمار) از این دسته محسوب میشن.

تراجنسیتی (transgender) : این دسته افراد، جنسیت متفاوت از جنس دارن (یعنی بدن نر دارند و خودشون رو زن میدونن یا بدن ماده دارند و خودشون رو مرد میدونن!) ولی دغدغه رسیدن به اون «جنس» رو ندارن.

تراجنسی (transexual ) : این افراد در واقع یک زیرمجموعه از تراجنسیتی ها محسوب میشن، تفاوت جنس و جنسیت رو در خودشان دیدند و شدیدا تمایل به این دارند که جنس هم همسو با جنسیت کنند. به همین جهت جراحی تطبیق جنس (srs) رو انجام می‌دن. البته، در خیلی از کشورهای جهان برای تراجنسیتی‌ها هم، الزام در جراحی تطبیق جنس وجود داره.

جنسیت شناور (genderfluid) : این افراد، میتونن گاهی خودشون رو زن و گاهی خودشون رو مرد بدونن. که البته، این نه بیماریه و نه عیب و ایراد و حتی الزامی هم در تغییرات ظاهری ایجاد نمی‌کنه.

دوجنسیتی (bigender ) : این افراد، هم‌زمان خودشون رو مرد و زن میدونن. تفاوتشون با جنسیت شناور هم در اینه که همیشه همزمان مرد و زن هستند که البته این موضوع هم اصلا بیولوژیکی نیست و روان‌شناختیه.

بی‌جنسیت (agender) این افراد، خودشون رو متعلق به هیچ جنسیتی نمیدونن. یعنی نه مرد هستند نه زن. معمولا هم ضمیر they به جای he/she استفاده میکنند.

جنسیت عجیب (genderqueer ) این دسته، افرادی هستند که برای خودشون جنسیت قائلند اما در هیچ کدوم از جنسیت های نامبرده بالا، نمیگنجن. به همین دلیل، بهشون جندرکوییر یا جنسیت عجیب گفته میشه.

همه‌جنسیتی (pan-gender) افرادی هستند که تمام دسته های بالا همزمان میتونن باشن. یکم عجیب و بدتعریفه ولی بهرحال، افرادی هستند که خودشون رو اینطور معرفی کنن.

چرا باید این ها رو بدونیم؟

دنیای امروز، دنیای رهایی از بسیاری از کلیشه هاست. مثلا رشته های دانشگاهی تفکرشون بین رشته‌ای شده، کسی که میره سراغ علوم کامپیوتر الزاما در علوم کامپیوتر درجا نمیزنه، بلکه ممکنه از علوم کامپیوتر در پزشکی هم استفاده کنه. از اونجایی که تمام زمینه هایی که داریم کلیشه ها دارن از بین برده میشن، در مورد جنسیت هم باید این اتفاق بیفته. امیدوارم بتونم با مطالبی که مینوسیم، نقش کوچکی در از بین بردن کلیشه ها، ایفا کنم.
#lgbt #metoo

) ولی دغدغه رسیدن به اون « جنس » رو ندارن . تراجنسی ( transexual ) : این افراد در واقع یک زیرمجموعه از تراجنسیتی ها محسوب میشن، تفاوت جنس و جنسیت رو در خودشان دیدند و شدیدا تمایل به این دارند که جنس هم همسو با جنسیت کنند . به همین جهت جراحی تطبیق جنس ( sr ) رو انجام می‌دن . البته، در خیلی از کشورهای جهان برای تراجنسیتی‌ها هم، الزام در جراحی تطبیق جنس وجود داره . جنسیت شناور ( genderfluid ) : این افراد، میتونن گاهی خودشون رو زن و گاهی خودشون رو مرد بدونن . که البته، این نه بیماریه و نه عیب و ایراد و حتی الزامی هم در تغییرات ظاهری ایجاد نمی‌کنه . دوجنسیتی ( bigender ) : این افراد، هم‌زمان خودشون رو مرد و زن میدونن . تفاوتشون با جنسیت شناور هم در اینه که همیشه همزمان مرد و زن هستند که البته این موضوع هم اصلا بیولوژیکی نیست و روان‌شناختیه . بی‌جنسیت ( agender ) این افراد، خودشون رو متعلق به هیچ جنسیتی نمیدونن . یعنی نه مرد هستند نه زن . معمولا هم ضمیر به جای he/she استفاده میکنند . جنسیت عجیب ( genderqueer ) این دسته، افرادی هستند که برای خودشون جنسیت قائلند اما در هیچ کدوم از جنسیت های نامبرده بالا، نمیگنجن . به همین دلیل، بهشون جندرکوییر یا جنسیت عجیب گفته میشه . همه‌جنسیتی ( pan-gender ) افرادی هستند که تمام دسته های بالا همزمان میتونن باشن . یکم عجیب و بدتعریفه ولی بهرحال، افرادی هستند که خودشون رو اینطور معرفی کنن . چرا باید این ها رو بدونیم؟ دنیای امروز، دنیای رهایی از بسیاری از کلیشه هاست . مثلا رشته های دانشگاهی تفکرشون بین رشته‌ای شده، کسی که میره سراغ علوم کامپیوتر الزاما در علوم کامپیوتر درجا نمیزنه، بلکه ممکنه از علوم کامپیوتر در پزشکی هم استفاده کنه . از اونجایی که تمام زمینه هایی که داریم کلیشه ها دارن از بین برده میشن، در مورد جنسیت هم باید این اتفاق بیفته . امیدوارم بتونم با مطالبی که مینوسیم، نقش کوچکی در از بین بردن کلیشه ها، ایفا کنم .
